# Vue + Quasar Conventions

## SFC Structure
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
// imports, composables, logic
</script>

<template>
  <!-- markup -->
</template>

<style scoped lang="scss">
/* component-specific overrides only */
</style>
```

- **No** `export default defineComponent()` — setup script only
- **No** `defineComponent` wrapper — `<script setup>` makes it unnecessary

## Props & Emits
```ts
// ✅ typed inline
const props = defineProps<{ examId: string; readonly?: boolean }>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ submit: [id: string]; cancel: [] }>()

// ✅ two-way binding
const model = defineModel<string>()
```

## Quasar Components
- Prefer `QBtn` over `<button>`, `QInput` over `<input>`, `QCard` over `<div class="card">`, etc.
- Use `QLayout` + `QPage` for page-level structure
- Use Quasar's `useQuasar()` for dialogs, notify, loading — not custom implementations

## Pinia in Components
```ts
// ✅ always destructure with storeToRefs for reactivity
const examStore = useExamStore()
const { currentExam, isLoading } = storeToRefs(examStore)
```

## i18n
```ts
const { t } = useI18n()
// ✅
<QBtn :label="t('exam.start')" />
// ❌
<QBtn label="Start Exam" />
```

## Routing
```ts
const router = useRouter()
const route = useRoute()
// Use named routes, not hardcoded paths
router.push({ name: 'exam-take', params: { id: examId } })
```
